meanings.definition: To laugh louder or more than someone else.
meanings.sent1: During the comedy show, Sarah outlaughed everyone in the audience.
meanings.sent2: She always outlaughed her friends at jokes.
meanings.sent3: At the party, Tom outlaughed his own joke, making everyone burst into laughter.
meanings.sent4: Her infectious laughter outlaughed the sound of the fireworks.
meanings.sent5: The little girl outlaughed the clown, spreading joy all around.

meanings.definition: Past tense of outlaugh: laughed louder or more than someone else.
meanings.sent1: Last night, he outlaughed his brother at the funny movie.
meanings.sent2: She outlaughed everyone at the comedy club last week.
meanings.sent3: The baby outlaughed her parents, finding everything hilarious.
meanings.sent4: His booming laughter outlaughed the thunderstorm outside.
meanings.sent5: The comedian outlaughed the audience, leaving them in stitches.
